This guide will only work for fedora atomic distro. Please execute code at your own risk.

Prerequisites:
0. Have a luks partition

1. find luks partition (not crypt, the part one containing it)
lsblk -o NAME,UUID,TYPE,MOUNTPOINT

2. check if your pc supports safe boot + tpm2

Setup tpm2:

1
sudo rpm-ostree initramfs --enable

2
sudo systemd-cryptenroll --tpm2-device=auto --tpm2-pcrs=0+1+7 /dev/nvme1n1p3

3
sudo nano /etc/crypttab

luks-<leave_the_id> UUID=<leave_the_id> none discard,tpm2-device=auto,tpm2-pcrs=0+1+7

4.

rpm-ostree initramfs-etc --force-sync


5. reboot and enjoy TPM2.0 working :)




If for whatever reason you need to re-enroll:

wipe slot (you can find the slot using sudo cryptsetup luksDump /dev/nvme1n1p3)

sudo systemd-cryptenroll --wipe-slot=tpm2 /dev/nvme1n1p3
